        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 1:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The expression, \"do not lie,\" which is harsh to us, accords with the plain, straightforward simplicity of ancient speech. It would not mean more than \"deceive\" (compare the marginal reference). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
